BT /F1 10.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 309.20 Tm (Four cards: DriverManager, Connection, PreparedStatement, ResultSet, each with a one-line role. A note) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 295.70 Tm (with the chain analogy.) Tj ET
0.720 0.720 0.760 rg 58.00 282.20 3.00 49.00 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 272.20 Tm (SAY \(read aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 256.20 Tm (These four interfaces are the spine of every JDBC program, so let's meet them. DriverManager is) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 241.20 Tm (a utility class: you give it a URL and credentials, and it returns a Connection. A Connection is one) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 226.20 Tm (open session with the database. Creating it opens a real network socket, so it is precious - you) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 211.20 Tm (must always close it. A PreparedStatement is a pre-compiled, parameterised SQL query with) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 196.20 Tm (question-mark placeholders. It is safe and fast, and you will use it for everything. And a ResultSet) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 181.20 Tm (is a cursor over the rows that a SELECT returns - you call r-s dot next to walk forward one row at a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 166.20 Tm (time. The note ties them together as a chain: DriverManager gets you a Connection; from the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 151.20 Tm (connection you create a PreparedStatement; running a SELECT on it gives you a ResultSet to) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 136.20 Tm (read.) Tj ET
