BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 664.00 Tm (SAY \(read aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 648.00 Tm (This is the recipe behind every JDBC program - keep it in mind for the entire lab. Step one:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 633.00 Tm (register the driver, with Class dot forName. This is automatic in JDBC 4 and later, but we show it) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 618.00 Tm (so you understand what is happening. Step two: open a connection, with DriverManager dot) Tj ET
