BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 387.30 Tm (SAY \(read aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 371.30 Tm (Let's place JDBC in the bigger picture honestly. Code volume: raw JDBC is high - you write the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 356.30 Tm (SQL and map the ResultSet by hand. Spring Data JPA is low - often just a method name or an) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 341.30 Tm (annotation. Control: JDBC gives you full control to write any SQL you want. JPA gives moderate) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 326.30 Tm (control, with JPQL and the at-Query annotation for custom cases. Learning curve: JDBC is low -) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 311.30 Tm (just SQL and four interfaces. JPA is higher, because you need JPA concepts first. Best for: JDBC) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 296.30 Tm (suits legacy systems and complex hand-tuned SQL; JPA suits most modern applications. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 281.30 Tm (takeaway: you learn JDBC to understand the foundation, and you use Spring Data JPA to build) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 266.30 Tm (efficiently on top of it.) Tj ET
